oman is referred to as both <i>Mabilia</i> and <i>Amabilia</i> in a document of  1185 ), but a short vowel in the resulting first syllable was standard, giving a rhyme with <i>babble</i>, until the 19th century, when people began to pronounce the name to rhyme with <i>table</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":18,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Mabel Lancaster was born about 1437, in Westmorland, England, her father, William Lancaster Knt., was 94 and her mother, Margaret Strickland, was 21. She had at least 3 sons and 2 daughters with Hugh Lowther. She was buried in Lowther, Westmorland, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1437–1475":"umbes 1437–1475","1437–1475":"1437–1475","1429–1475":"1429–1475","1458–1524":"1458–1524","1461–1510":"1461–1510","1463–1511":"1463–1511","1465–Female":"1465–Surnud","1472–Male":"1472–Surnud","1345–Male":"1345–Surnud","1417–Female":"1417–Surnud","1472":"1472","1461":"1461","15 August 1461":"15. august 1461","1437":"1437","1524":"1524","1458":"1458","1511":"1511","about 1437":"umbes 1437","1455":"1455","1345":"1345","1510":"1510","1465":"1465","1475":"1475","about 1458":"umbes 1458","1463":"1463","1429":"1429","1417":"1417","Lowther, Westmorland, England":"Lowther, Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lowther Castle, Lowther, Westmorland, England":"Lowther Castle, Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lowther Hall, Lowther, Westmoreland, England":"Lowther, Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hartsop, Westmorland,